    "Religion Both with and without a system prompt, 'religion' obtains among the highest regard scores (Fig. 3).",
    "Refusal rates for religion are again highest for Llama, followed by Mistral and Qwen (Fig. 1).",
    "When looked at separately, certain religious groups trigger refusals at high rates, e.g., Jews for Llama, Mistral, and Starling (App F, Fig. 5).",
    "Responses for atheists, Mormons, and Muslims are characterised by lower sentiment across models, while Buddhists, Catholics, Protestants, and Christians score high (App F, Fig. 6).",
    "Starling scores maximally on the sentiment score for Christians, Catholics, and Protestants."
